===Background===
Duncan was the eldest son and heir of King [[Aegon V Targaryen]]. He was named in honor of his father's great friend Ser [[Duncan the Tall]], who had also become [[Lord Commander]] of Aegon V's [[Kingsguard]]. He died alongside his father and his namesake in the [[Tragedy at Summerhall]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Oathkeeper]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
He is mentioned in his namesake's entry in ''[[The Book of Brothers]]''.

